@node Amipeg
@title "aMiPEG 1.1"

 aMiPEG

 Last version: 1.1
 Last changes: since 1.0 (04.I.98)
               new: PicassoIV-PIP with YCrCb-RGB + Scaling (by Tobias Seiler),
                    doc updated
               fix: PIPE: works again, LOOP mode in HAM8, some stream parser
                    fixes
 Locations   : Aminet aminet/gfx/show/aMiPEG_1.1_bin.lha
               The official aMiPEG WWW (look below)
 Arch. size  : 96 kb
 Program type: MPEG animations player
               Supported Video formats:
                 MPEG-1 Video
                 MPEG-1 Video System Streams
               Supported Audio formats:
                 ---
 Requirements:
               Hardware:
                 - Amiga with OCS/ECS/AGA/CGFX
                 - Kickstart 2.04+
                 - mc68020 or Faster
                 - around 1 meg of free memory (FAST recommented)
               Software:
                 - asyncio.library 0.8+
               Recommended:
                 - mc68040/40Mhz
                 - CyberGFX 3.0+
 Output type :
               Graphics:
                 - color         lores HAM8 screen
                 - hiresham      hires HAM8 screen (better but slower)
                 - ham6          for OCS users
                 - cybergfx      15/16/24-bit CyberGraphX display
                 - cybergfxgray  gray display on 15/16/24-bit screen
                 - gray          gray display on 8-bit screen
                 - vlayer        display using video overlay of CV64/3D
                 - vlayergray    as above, in gray
                 - none          no display at all
               Audio:
                 ---
 Author      :
               Snail:
                 Miloslaw Smyk
                 ul. Orawska 22/34
                 70-131 Szczecin
                 POLAND
               Phone:
                 ---
               E-Mail:
                 thorgal@amiga.com.pl
                 thorgal@wfmh.man.szczecin.pl
               WWW:
                 http://amiga.com.pl/amipeg
               Other:
                 ---
 Prog. status: Freeware
 Future      : 
               MPEG audio - now when mpega.library is available it should be easy
               96 pixels or 80 pixels wide animations look awful.
               New scaling modes are not ready yet.
               MPEG-2 (but it may happened in completly new player - frogger now)
 Other infos :
               asyncio I/O, fast output modes in HAM
               There is also a NEWSGROUP aMiPEG, you can subscribe.
               write on:
                amipeg-request@amiga.com.pl
                and as EMail body write:
                subscribe <your-email>

@endnode

