@node MPEGdatatype
@title "MPEG Video Datatype 1.11"

 MPEG Vide Datatype

 Last version: 1.11
 Last changes: 1.10 (16.XI.97)
               new: enabled NOLOADALL
               fix: some parts of stack usage and CyberGFX safety
 Locations   : Aminet aminet/util/dtype/mpvdtc018.lha
 Arch. size  : 250 kb
 Program type: MPEG animations analyzer and tester
               Supported Video formats:
                 MPEG-1 Video
               Supported Audio formats:
                 audio.device (required separate decoder)
 Requirements:
               Hardware:
                 - Kickstart 3.04+
                 - mc68020 or Faster
                 -  Much  memory (at least 2MB (I think... (test report
                    recommned))  (or the "vmm.library" V3.0 from Martin
                    Apel's VMM package.
               Software:
                 - "datatypes/animation.datatype", >= V39.
                   "animation.datatype 40.7 (28.09.93)" requires itself
                    some libraries/boopsi
                 - "realtime.library", >= V39  - for timing
                 - "gadgets/tapedeck.gadget" - for the controls
                 -  The  IEEE  versions  (#?ieee  directories) requires
                    the "mathieeedoubbas.library" (V38 or higher) library
                    in your LIBS:  (or something equal) directory.
               Recommended:
                 ---
 Output type :
               Graphics:
                 - Ordered       dither type
                 - Color         ECS/AGA
                 - HAM6          ECS
                 - HAM8          AGA
                 - 16/26BIT      GFX card required
                 - GRAY          ECS/AGA
                 - EHB           ECS
               Audio:
                 ---
 Author      :
               Snail:
                 Roland Mainz
                 Hohenstaufenstraße 8
                 52388 Nörvenich
                 GERMANY
               Phone:
                 (+49)(0)2426/901568
               E-Mail:
                 GISBURN@w-specht.rhein-ruhr.de
               WWW:
                 ---
               Other:
                 ---
 Prog. status: Freeware
 Future      : 
               Following will be implemented in one of the later versions:
               - Fix some inconsistensies
               - More time to rework this and other public projects
               - To write a "real" #?.guide file (and clean up the docs...)
 Other infos :
               You may use VMM.library for virtual momory to preload
               MPEG or just play it directly from file

@endnode

